{
    "name": "Prisoner",
    "type": "npc",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Prisoner",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "Most who end up in a jail, dungeon, or prison are just biding their time until their imprisonment ends, trying to find ways to make it through interminable days of boredom and deprivation. Some, however, may use their time on the inside to strengthen their criminal connections. Using force and intimidation to gain status among other prisoners, they create makeshift weapons to take down their enemies and give them an edge if escape becomes possible. Even for prisoners who don't become involved in the world of prison politics, learning to stand up for themselves and projecting an air of toughness can become essential for survival in a place where people have little left to lose.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Humanoid</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"14\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Society</a></u>)</b>: DC 15",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 215",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 215",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 215
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Downtrodden",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Braving The Mob",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "A mob is a <a aonid=\"618\" game-obj=\"Rules\">violent crowd</a> that works as greater difficult terrain and hazardous terrain, dealing 1d4 damage for each square entered. A creature can spend a single action to attempt a DC 16 <a aonid=\"7\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Intimidation</a> check, clearing the mob from all squares adjacent to them on a success (or all squares within 10 feet on a critical success). This action has the <a aonid=\"32\" game-obj=\"Traits\">concentrate</a>, <a aonid=\"60\" game-obj=\"Traits\">emotion</a>, <a aonid=\"104\" game-obj=\"Traits\">manipulate</a>, and <a aonid=\"106\" game-obj=\"Traits\">mental</a> traits.",
                    "sources": {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 214",
                            "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 214",
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                        },
                        "page": 214
                    },
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "advice_and_rules",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Advice and Rules",
                    "image": "Sidebar_1_AdviceAndRules.png"
                },
                {
                    "name": "Word On The Street",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Privy to all sorts of conversations from passersby, the downtrodden can provide eyes and ears on the street. Finding a reliable contact can give a character a circumstance bonus to checks to <a aonid=\"49\" game-obj=\"Actions\">Gather Information</a> if they return to that source. This bonus is usually +1, but could be +2 or +3 if the contact lingers in a market where influential politicians shop, sweeps a noble estate, or the like.<br/><br/> Befriending NPCs in advance can also help the heroes in action scenes. A friendly urchin might show a character a shortcut to catch an escaping enemy, a crowd of fans who frequent a bard's performances might throw rocks to distract someone trying to fight the bard, and so on.",
                    "sources": {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 214",
                            "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 214",
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                        },
                        "page": 214
                    },
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "advice_and_rules",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Advice and Rules",
                    "image": "Sidebar_1_AdviceAndRules.png"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Unfortunately, every society has people living on its fringes. While good communities work to grant aid and respite to their downtrodden, sometimes\u2014due to economic downturn, famine, or war\u2014the ranks of the less fortunate exceed the community's capacity to support them. In heartless neutral and evil societies, poverty is seen as an inevitability that can never be truly eradicated, or even worse, as a tool to be manipulated for political gain.",
            "sources": {
                "type": "source",
                "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                "link": {
                    "type": "link",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 214",
                    "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 214",
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                },
                "page": 214
            }
        }
    ],
